{
  "texts": [
    "This modul touches upon topics such as barrier-free software design, mechanisms and reasons for digitalised discrimination or biases in corporate practices (their homepage specifically alludes to the fact that input and output devices, such as VR glasses, have exclusively undergone testing with male test subjects and that the development of digital products and services is predominantly carried out by men.",
    "The practical ramifications of such a bias result in input and output devices that are less appropriate for women and children) (Technische Universität Berlin, 2023).",
    "Columbia recommends the practice of \"scaffolding\", which is the process of breaking down a larger assignment into subtasks (Columbia University, 2023).",
    "In their understanding, this method facilitates regular check-ins and enables students to receive timely feedback throughout the learning process.",
    "Simultaneously, the implementation of scaffolding helps instructors become more familiar with students and their work as the semester progresses, allowing them to take additional steps in the case of students who might need more attention due to their vulnerable backgrounds or disabilities to complete the same tasks."
  ]
}